WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:04.467
<i>♪ Thank you for bein' a friend ♪</i>

00:05.567 --> 00:08.500
<i>♪ Traveled down the road and back again ♪</i>

00:09.567 --> 00:11.367
<i>♪ Your heart is true ♪</i>

00:11.433 --> 00:15.367
<i>♪ You're a pal and a confidante ♪</i>

00:16.367 --> 00:19.133
<i>♪ And if you threw a party ♪</i>

00:19.800 --> 00:23.467
<i>♪ Invited everyone you knew ♪</i>

00:24.734 --> 00:28.734
<i>♪ You would see the biggest gift</i>
<i>Would be from me ♪</i>

00:28.800 --> 00:31.667
<i>♪ And the card attached would say ♪</i>

00:31.734 --> 00:37.834
<i>♪ "Thank you for bein' a friend" ♪</i>

00:41.233 --> 00:47.533
(mellow music playing)

01:00.533 --> 01:03.200
-You couldn't sleep either, Dorothy?
-No, Rose.

01:03.266 --> 01:06.700
Are you upset because Blanche
is selling the house?

01:06.767 --> 01:11.233
No, I'm upset because Joe Piscopo
didn't get the lead role in <i>Rain Man.</i>

01:12.433 --> 01:15.033
Of course, I'm upset about the house.

01:17.033 --> 01:19.900
Ma, it's 2 am, where have you been?

01:19.967 --> 01:23.734
I stuffed pillows under the sheets
to fool you during bed check.

01:23.800 --> 01:25.633
What is this, <i>Stalag 17</i>?

01:26.300 --> 01:32.333
-I couldn't sleep. I had a nightmare.
-Tell me about it. I can interpret dreams.

01:32.400 --> 01:36.066
Blanche sold the house,
and I wound up back at shady pines.

01:37.367 --> 01:38.734
This is a tough one.

01:39.333 --> 01:40.934
Dorothy, don't send me back!

01:41.033 --> 01:44.467
Ma, I'm not sending you
back to shady pines.

01:44.533 --> 01:47.800
Oh, my God.
She found a cheaper home!

01:47.867 --> 01:51.333
Blanche, please,
please, don't sell the house.

01:52.200 --> 01:54.600
What the hell is that
holding up your stockings?

01:55.934 --> 01:57.467
Get out of there.

01:57.967 --> 02:01.433
I know I told Mr. Yakamora
I'd sell the house,

02:01.500 --> 02:04.400
but it's not fair
to make that decision by myself.

02:04.467 --> 02:07.166
Tell me what to do.

02:07.233 --> 02:10.900
It's your house, Blanche.
You have to decide.

02:10.967 --> 02:15.533
Since when have you all been so shy?
We always tell each other what to do.

02:17.166 --> 02:19.367
-Honey, are you all right?
-I'll be fine.

02:19.934 --> 02:20.967
Is this about Arnie?

02:21.033 --> 02:25.133
No, Blanche, she's upset because
they keep changing the taste of coke.

02:32.033 --> 02:35.800
Arnie wants me to go away with him.
On a cruise to The Bahamas.

02:36.333 --> 02:37.333
Oh.

02:37.800 --> 02:41.166
Oh, and you're upset because he
wants you to pay your own way?

02:43.934 --> 02:47.700
I'm upset because we'll be all alone
in the middle of the ocean,

02:47.767 --> 02:51.934
on a ship, in a state room...
with a bed.

02:53.633 --> 02:54.834
Oh.

02:55.300 --> 02:56.867
I don't know what to do.

02:57.567 --> 02:58.700
I haven't...

02:59.567 --> 03:01.166
been with a man...

03:01.700 --> 03:06.333
-in that special way since Charlie died.
-Get out of here.

03:09.633 --> 03:10.900
Well, it's true.

03:11.533 --> 03:13.333
Charlie was the only lover I ever had

03:13.400 --> 03:15.734
and my first time was
on our wedding night.

03:15.800 --> 03:18.233
Get out of here.

03:18.767 --> 03:20.700
Oh, back off, Blanche.

03:20.767 --> 03:24.166
Not all of us are classified
by the navy as a friendly port.

03:28.600 --> 03:30.567
Maybe it sounds strange but...

03:31.233 --> 03:34.100
without Charlie, I thought that part
of my life was over.

03:34.166 --> 03:36.900
-I never gave it a second thought.
-Until now.

03:38.367 --> 03:40.200
Then I think you should
go on the cruise.

03:40.266 --> 03:42.767
Honey, if the situation is right,
you'll know it.

03:43.500 --> 03:44.633
But I'm not sure I'm ready.

03:44.700 --> 03:47.333
Oh, honey, I know what you're going
through.

03:47.400 --> 03:50.333
The bottom line is:
If you take a chance in life

03:50.400 --> 03:53.467
sometimes good things happen,
sometimes bad things happen.

03:53.533 --> 03:56.233
But, honey, if you don't take a chance,
nothing happens.

03:59.166 --> 04:00.467
I'm gonna take a chance.

04:00.533 --> 04:02.633
-Wonderful.
-Great.

04:02.700 --> 04:04.533
Oh, I have to look in my closet,

04:04.600 --> 04:07.600
I don't even know what to wear
the first night on the ship.

04:07.667 --> 04:09.734
A lifejacket and a great big smile.

04:13.800 --> 04:16.000
I wonder what Rose is doing right now?

04:16.066 --> 04:18.533
You mean you wonder
if she's doing it right now.

04:19.934 --> 04:23.600
I hope we didn't push her
into something too fast.

04:23.667 --> 04:28.200
How in the world did she manage
to wait 15 years?

04:29.033 --> 04:33.500
-How long did you wait after George died?
-Till the paramedics came.

04:33.567 --> 04:34.633
Ma.

04:42.834 --> 04:46.333
What about you, Dorothy?
Who was the first after Stan?

04:46.400 --> 04:49.233
-Blanche...
-Her divorce lawyer.

04:49.900 --> 04:53.200
-How did you know?
-It's always the divorce lawyer.

04:54.500 --> 04:59.066
It was terrible.
I'd gone on an eating binge

04:59.133 --> 05:02.734
and put on quite a bit of weight,
plus I was not a 20-year-old.

05:03.000 --> 05:08.500
When you're 20, no matter what you do,
everything stays where it's supposed to.

05:08.967 --> 05:10.734
Now, when you lean over

05:10.800 --> 05:14.033
it looks like somebody's let the air
out of your face.

05:16.867 --> 05:21.467
-What?
-Lean over a mirror and look at yourself.

05:21.533 --> 05:24.100
-Where's a mirror.
-In the tool drawer.

05:24.166 --> 05:27.066
You'd better take
a sedative before you look.

05:27.700 --> 05:32.533
I look at my face all the time.
How different could it be leaning over?

05:33.000 --> 05:34.967
Oh, my God!

05:35.600 --> 05:39.734
Oh, my God, Dorothy!
Why didn't you tell me about this before?

05:40.700 --> 05:43.266
Only on your back, Blanche.

05:43.333 --> 05:47.567
That way everything slides back and you
look like you've just had a facelift.

05:49.567 --> 05:51.433
Oh, you're right. I'm gorgeous.

05:52.967 --> 05:55.233
I'm going to have to meet men lying down.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.100
I thought you did.

06:01.300 --> 06:05.033
Of course, that way,
not only does your face fall back,

06:05.100 --> 06:06.767
but your chest does, too.

06:08.433 --> 06:12.500
Unfortunately, it falls back
and off to the side.

06:17.567 --> 06:21.967
-We might as well get some sleep.
-I can't sleep.

06:22.033 --> 06:25.467
I'm wound up tighter than the girdle
on a Baptist minister's wife

06:25.533 --> 06:27.767
at a pancake breakfast.

06:28.834 --> 06:30.633
Wow, that tight.

06:32.166 --> 06:38.767
Back in St. Olaf, when I couldn't sleep,
I'd have a glass of warm milk,

06:38.834 --> 06:42.867
slip under the covers,
and count cows jumping over my bed.

06:43.734 --> 06:45.533
It usually worked like a charm...

06:46.000 --> 06:49.800
except when a cow with a low udder

06:49.867 --> 06:52.667
would brush across my forehead
and wake me up.

06:54.300 --> 06:58.700
I don't know what I'm going to do.
I'm torn and confused.

06:59.300 --> 07:01.333
I'll have to think about it tomorrow.

07:01.667 --> 07:05.400
-After all, tomorrow's another day.
-Calm down, Scarlet.

07:05.467 --> 07:10.934
-There's no need to be so dramatic.
-Everyone around here acts like a ham.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.533
There's been more
bad acting, bad dancing,

07:13.600 --> 07:17.000
and bad singing under this roof
than a Suzanne Somer's special.

07:19.033 --> 07:24.300
(peppy music playing)

07:26.934 --> 07:28.000
Rose.

07:32.734 --> 07:33.967
Blanche.

07:38.533 --> 07:41.367
-Dorothy.
-Go, Dorothy, go!

07:52.033 --> 07:54.900
Gosh, I didn't realize
how long Dorothy's solo is.

07:57.266 --> 08:00.200
I sure hope the doctor says
she's going to be all right.

08:10.333 --> 08:12.266
I won't dance. Don't ask me.

08:13.233 --> 08:14.266
Pay attention.

08:14.834 --> 08:17.767
-You're in for a treat.
-Ma, not another act.

08:17.834 --> 08:20.233
Not just another act. The act.

08:20.300 --> 08:23.600
I've taken a classic
and reworked it Sophia-style.

08:26.233 --> 08:29.066
(music plays)

08:29.133 --> 08:31.967
♪ <i>Thanks for the Medicare</i> ♪

08:34.900 --> 08:37.233
♪ <i>For blue cross and blue shield</i> ♪

08:37.300 --> 08:39.133
♪ <i>For a hip that finally healed</i> ♪

08:40.633 --> 08:42.800
♪ <i>Remember on prescriptions</i> ♪

08:42.867 --> 08:45.166
♪ <i>Generic is a steal</i> ♪

08:45.233 --> 08:49.700
♪ <i>We thank you so much</i> ♪

08:55.967 --> 08:59.433
What do you think?
I can take the criticism.

09:03.300 --> 09:04.633
Depressing.

09:06.333 --> 09:07.333
Awful.

09:08.834 --> 09:10.033
Stinky.

09:12.500 --> 09:14.166
Go to hell, all of you!

09:18.367 --> 09:21.033
I won't have that filthy beast
in my house.

09:21.100 --> 09:24.900
-It belongs in a barnyard.
-This isn't a farm chicken.

09:24.967 --> 09:29.033
Count Bessie's a show biz chicken.
Watch this.

09:29.100 --> 09:32.233
A show biz chicken.
Does she play the piano?

09:33.300 --> 09:35.033
She plays the piano.

09:39.834 --> 09:44.400
-You just wait and see this.
-Ok, honey. Come on, it's Showtime.

09:44.767 --> 09:47.433
Yeah. Come on, sweetheart.
Oh, I know.

09:47.500 --> 09:51.567
Here we go. Ok, count, hit it.

09:51.633 --> 09:55.667
(plays "Old MacDonald")

09:58.266 --> 10:02.100
Isn't she incredible?
What do you say? Can she stay?

10:02.166 --> 10:05.133
I guess so. All right.

10:05.200 --> 10:07.500
Just be sure and keep her in her cage.

10:07.567 --> 10:10.200
Maybe I can convince the count

10:10.266 --> 10:12.967
to give us some
live entertainment with dessert.

10:13.500 --> 10:16.633
-Have you any requests?
-How about "Bye Bye, Birdie"?

10:19.300 --> 10:21.800
Girls, girls, count Bessie is missing.

10:24.467 --> 10:27.867
I went out to the garage to feed her,
and her cage was empty.

10:27.934 --> 10:29.266
Where could she be?

10:47.100 --> 10:48.967
Aunt Angelo.

10:51.567 --> 10:54.900
-Where did you get this chicken?
-The garage.

10:57.600 --> 11:01.266
I guess this means no live entertainment
with dessert.

11:07.800 --> 11:10.633
-How did you do?
-We came in second.

11:10.700 --> 11:14.600
-That's terrific. What did you get?
-Treated badly.

11:15.633 --> 11:17.200
They told us to get out of the way

11:17.266 --> 11:19.667
when they took the winner's picture
with Anita Bryant.

11:20.300 --> 11:24.934
-I'd love to hear your song.
-Oh, forget it, Blanche.

11:25.000 --> 11:27.166
The whole experience was too painful.

11:27.233 --> 11:29.300
-Please.
-We want to forget it.

11:29.367 --> 11:30.800
-Please.
-Hit it, Rose.

